						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvūṟal-Mahādēva, by one <hi rend="bold">Naran Tuṅgappēraraiyaṉ</hi> of Puliyūr in Vaṇḍāḻai Vēḷūr-kūṟṟam a subdivision of Śōḻa-nāḍu. This is probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
